                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/3691<hi
                        rend="superscript">9/14</hi>: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Deputy Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bordeaux</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-16T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 16, 1940—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 16—3:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. My telegrams Nos. 3, June 15, 5 p.m., and 4, June 16, 1 a.m. Differences of
                    opinion continue within the Government. No decision was taken as to course of
                    action at this morning’s Cabinet meeting pending receipt of the British reply
                    which is expected to be delivered this afternoon. A further Council of Ministers
                    is scheduled to begin at 5:00 this evening.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Biddle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
